The paper deals with unsupervised object-oriented scene representation learning, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed model, SPACE, is a generative latent variable model that combines spatial-attention and scene-mixture approaches, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of parallel spatial-attention, which is a technique that can be related to neural networks (cs.NE).
